ed","75 g red peppers, cut in pieces","1 - 2 fresh jalapeño chillies, deseeded, to taste","500 g ripe mangoes, cut in small pieces (1-2 cm)","2 tsp fine sea salt","100 g sugar","250 g water"]}],"id":"r150899","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-PwMVdYMnSL8\/XZQwpV9xh5I\/AAAAAAAAcnQ\/lziED7Q01S8pPJejXiHdW3xUJ8cm8I71QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_cZcNSIKNxS0JpMmX.png","title":"Honey Lime Chicken with Mango Chutney","publishedAt":"2017-06-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"43 g","fat":"1 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"31 g","calories":"1346 kJ \/ 321 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking paper, cling film, glass jar with screw-top lid, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Steaming this zesty chicken keeps the meat beautifully moist. Any leftover mango chutney can be stored in the fridge and served with your favourite Thermomix curry.","A chicken supreme is a breast of chicken with the wing bone still attached.","To prepare jar, place <b>500 g<b> water in mixing bowl. Place jar and lid upside down in the centre of the Varoma and steam <b><strong>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/strong>.<b>  Leave to drain - do not dry or touch the inside surfaces. Alternatively, thoroughly wash jar and lid in hot, soapy water. Rinse by pouring over boiling water. Prepare for filling, if needed, by placing on a clean tea towel in a roasting tin and heat in the oven at 100˚C until required.","Once cooled completely, mango chutney can be stored in the fridge for up to <b>2 weeks<b> or in freezer-proof containers in the freezer for up to <b>6 months.<b> Serve with steamed meat or fish, your favourite cheese, or a curry.","For a stronger flavour, marinate chicken in <b>step 2<b> for a few hours or overnight.","For a complete meal, in <b>step 5<b> steam in Varoma dish <b>400-600 g vegetables<b> (e.g. carrots, potatoes, green beans, courgettes, broccoli), cut in bite-size pieces, until cooked as desired."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h 15m","4 portions"]}